<br>
When in one of my &quot;level 60&quot; moods, I tried to solo the Cliff Golem.  I got him to 8%, then ran out of mana to keep healing the pet.  I was using epic pet, with all the gear a level 60 mage can summon on him.  I was chaining the 44th and 52 heals.  I also have SCM3 and Mend Companion so they helped.  I think I would have killed him if I had lvl 60 pet heal.  The only &quot;questionable&quot; thing about soloing the Cliff Golem was I had KEI.  Since I have flowing thought 1, I'll consider that a gear difference.  LOL.  I also was on a horse for the whole fight.<br>
<br>
I really want to solo the Cliff Golem while level 60.  I don't know what I'm doing wrong or what I can change at this point.  Perhaps the other mages could solo him just because they have more FT and their mana pool was bigger.  My mana pool of 3600 and FT1 was definately a limitation.  Also, I would DEFINATELY have easily won if I could keep clicking mana rods to replace mana.  I can only get 1 mana rod click in the duration of that fight, and I had HP for like 3-4 more clicks.<br>
<br>
I tried to solo the Priest of Discord in Gfay.  He was nearly immune to my spells, so I just aggro kited him with epic pet.  I got him to 45% and I was still full HP and mana.  I had cast like 5 pets by that point.  Then suddenly, he disappeared.  He popped back to his spawn point next to the guards with no aggro and full health.  The weird part was, I could not see him!  I had a newbie target him, then I assisted, and he popped back into my screen.  I pulled him again and started trying to solo him again.   When he disappeared for the 2nd time at 70% HP, I just gave up.<br>
