<br>
-Extra FT VI from items<br>
-The level 60 pet heal<br>
-Another 400 mana in my pool<br>
-Improved healing III item<br>
-Gloves of Dark summoning (make epic better)<br>
-Frenzied Burnout<br>
<br>
Having said that, I have a new tactic I need to try out.  Mala the Golem, then kite until mana is back, then Nuke with 57 shock till he is 95% (does not summon yet).  Then kite to med back mana, when at full, send in pet and aggro kite him.  He will start summoning, and get a few pops into me before the pet takes aggro.  I did this last night and he finally started into the pet when I was at 70% HP, but Full mana and the Golem was at 91%.  Then I can fight him the same way as before and I think I can kill him.  I'll try this soon.<br>
<br>
Also, I played around with chain casting a pet on him.  I have not yet succeeded.  I forced him to summon my pet by using...<br>
/pet follow<br>
/pet hold<br>
/pet attack<br>
After he summoned the pet, I immediately started casting the new pet, hoping I could pop it out before his &quot;summon timer&quot; reset.  No luck, he summoned me everytime.  His summon timer must be like 5-7 seconds.  But I have another idea I can try.  I'm going to try this...<br>
<br>
Let him chew up a pet for a bit, then...<br>
/pet follow<br>
/start casting 61 air pet<br>
wait 2 sec<br>
type /pet hold<br>
wait for pet to be summoned<br>
/pet attack (to keep him on pet and not me)<br>
/pet get lost (before new one pops out)<br>
<br>
This will have to happen very fast, all within a few seconds.  So it will be challenging, much more challenging the the age old tactic of just chaining a pet.  But I think this will work and I'm going to experiment with it.  IF this does work, it will give me some tools to chain cast pets on summoning mobs... Very usefull. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
